"True art wrote Henry David Thoreau, "is but the expression of our love of nature." No artist embodies this belief more than Eliot Porter. One of the masters of color photography Porter has awakened our senses and touched us deeply with his vision of nature. Now, at age of eighty-five, this poet of the camera reveals ... personal reminiscence a lifetime of discovery, adventure, and devotion to his art
